<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1584] setIncludeScore is added to the &quot;FL&quot; field instead of being concated</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1584</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current implementation of setIncludeScore(boolean) &lt;b&gt;adds&lt;/b&gt; the value &quot;score&quot; to the FL parameter.&lt;br/&gt;
This causes a problem when using the setFields followed by include score.&lt;br/&gt;
If I do this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;setFields(&quot;*&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
setIncludeScore(true);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would expect the outcome to be &quot;fl=*,score&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Instead the outcome is: &quot;fl=* &amp;amp;fl=score&quot; which fails to use the score field as FL is not a multi-valued field.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current implementation in the SolrJ SolrQuery object is:&lt;br/&gt;
add(&quot;fl&quot;, &quot;score&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
instead it should be:&lt;br/&gt;
set(&quot;fl&quot;, get(&quot;fl&quot;) + &quot;,score&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;obviously not as simplistic as that, but you catch my drift...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
